<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="726" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8612: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-24T12:00:00-06:00">November 24,
                                1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>233. Committees representing conservative and liberal supporters of
                            biparty agreement met yesterday and decided to abstain from voting on
                            December 8th thus virtually withdrawing Argüello-Espinosa ticket and
                            leaving Somoza as sole Presidential candidate.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>